<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Choi_Min-sik" title="Choi Min-sik">Choi Min-sik</a> as Oh Dae-su; he has been imprisoned for about 15 years. Choi Min-sik lost and gained weight for his role depending on the filming schedule, trained for six weeks and did most of his own stunt work.
<ul><li>Oh Tae-kyung as young Dae-su</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Yoo_Ji-tae" title="Yoo Ji-tae">Yoo Ji-tae</a> as Lee Woo-jin: The man behind Oh Dae-su's imprisonment. Park Chan-wook's ideal choice for Woo-jin had been actor <a href="/wiki/Han_Suk-kyu" title="Han Suk-kyu">Han Suk-kyu</a>, who previously played a rival to Choi Min-sik in <i><a href="/wiki/Shiri_(film)" title="Shiri (film)">Shiri</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/No._3" title="No. 3">No. 3</a></i>. Choi then suggested Yoo Ji-tae for the role, despite Park thinking him too young for the part.<sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Yoo_Yeon-seok" title="Yoo Yeon-seok">Yoo Yeon-seok</a> as young Woo-jin</li></ul></li>
